            "note": "qPCRcalculator is designed as a workflow that guides the user through calculation steps. It calculates individual sample efficiencies and the abundance of nucleic acids from Cq or Ct values using a standard curve. Normalization of target gene expression/abundance to reference gene(s) expression/abundance is performed. Input is TAB-delimited text with 3 rows: Sample_name, Cq and Relative quantity/Dilution.\nCq datatype: decimal number (dot . and comma are allowed) or integer.\nRelative quantity/Dilution datatype: decimal number or integer. TAB-delimited gene-sample matrix",
